&lt;p&gt;Pricing on seven pricing bases (PB1 to PB7) for a whole life book of a commercial life insurer in Spain, original dataset found at:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;https://www.openicpsr.org/openicpsr/project/178881/version/V1/view&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Policies are valued as at inception date, with a minimum age of 17 years.  The maximum age is 108.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AM92 mortality, constant premium and constant sum assured were assumed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No surrenders were assumed.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All premiums are the monthly premium payable upfront.  Contained in the DATA worksheet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ID = unique identifier per original DOI &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Age = actuarial age per original DOI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sum Assured = death benefit per original DOI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Term_if = term since contract started per original DOI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PB1 - PB7 = Monthly premium&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;META, BASES, SUMMARY worksheets contain more details.&lt;/p&gt;
